   STAFF PROFILES

   CATHERINE CLOSE, CHIEF COUNSEL

   Ms. Close was appointed as the first in-house attorney to the State
   Board of Control in 1989. Ms. Close provides legal advice to the Board
   Members, Executive Director, and program managers on all legal issues
   that affect the Board's Victims of Crime, Government Claims, and
   administrative programs, as well as the Revenue Recovery and Compliance
   Division.

   Ms. Close entered state service in 1978 as a staff counsel to the
   California Community Colleges Chancellor's Office. She later served as
   a staff counsel to the Waste Management Board. Prior to her state
   service, Ms. Close was employed with legal services organizations in
   the State of South Carolina and in Santa Barbara County.

   Ms. Close received Bachelor of Arts and Master of Arts degrees from the
   University of California, Davis. She received her Juris Doctor degree
   from the McGeorge School of Law in 1976.

